{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T11:03:34.193Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Encoder-Decoder — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Encoder-Decoder Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Encoder-Decoder architecture"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a fundamental framework in sequence-to-sequence (Seq2Seq) models that transforms one sequence of data into another sequence. It was designed to handle the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "input-output length problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": " where the input and output often have different lengths—for example, translating \"how are you\" (3 words in English) to \"comment allez-vous\" (5 words in French)."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Traditional neural networks struggled with flexible sizes, but encoder-decoder models handle them perfectly."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Encoder-Decoder Matters in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder-Decoder is the engine behind many generative AI applications:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Application"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How It Works"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"ty